            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_281gc' title='Col. 281GC &mdash; HL Deb 08 March 2005 vol 670 c281GC' name='column_281gc' href='#column_281gc' rel='bookmark'>281GC</a>
            is registered. Because it is a charity, it will seek repayment of any taxes possible and may therefore need a relationship with the Inland Revenue.</p><p>
            Therefore, if we were to go along with the amendment of the noble Lord, Lord Hodgson, would that mean that the Inland Revenue would have to do rather more to check whether a charity is a charity whereas, at the moment, it may just rely on registration and say, "If it is registered, we repay the money"? That is a further problem.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
