            I wanted to strike a balance and focus the commission on the areas of major risk, which are the big charities. For a charity with an annual income of below &#x00A3;25,000, I felt that public involvement&#x2014;and therefore public risk&#x2014;was very low, but I accept the points made. I hope that the Government may think again about the &#x00A3;5,000 and push it a bit further along the lines spoken about by the noble Lord, Lord Shutt. For the mean time, so long as the "may" and "must" issue can be resolved so that it is clear that charities can get on to the register if they wish and thereby access all the advantages to which the Minister referred, I beg leave to withdraw the amendment.</p><p>
            Amendment, by leave, withdrawn.
          </p>
